"Abstract As with just about all high-tech advances, information technology is a two-edged sword. None more so than the Internet. To extend the analogy, the Internet is seen by some as a Damoclean sword hanging over their countries. Some see it as a threat to their security and integrity. Others who are finding it an irresistible allure for doing business in global markets. It is, however, primarily the governments who are most wary of it and how it might empower the man-in-the-street."
